headline: Boeing Defense Workers Set to Strike Monday
summary: The union representing about 3,200 St. Louis-area workers has rejected the company’s latest contract offer.

headline: Boeing St. Louis defense workers set to strike from Monday after rejecting latest offer
summary: "IAM District 837 members ... deserve a contract that reflects their skill, dedication, and the critical role they play in our nation's defense," the union's Business Representative Tom Boelling said.  Boeing said it was ready for the action.  "We are prepared for a strike and have fully implemented our contingency plan," Boeing Air Dominance vice president and general manager Dan Gillian said in an emailed statement to Reuters.
